cs.DC, cs.DS, cs.PF, cs.PL, cs.SY

Reasoning: 
1. cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) - The paper is inspired by applications in parallel computing and analyzes work stealing in multithreaded computations, which falls under the scope of distributed and parallel computing. 
2. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) - The paper analyzes the maximum number of steals in rooted trees, which is a data structure commonly used in algorithms. 
3. cs.PF (Performance) - The paper analyzes the performance of work stealing in multithreaded computations and provides upper bounds on the number of steals, which is related to performance. 
4. cs.PL (Programming Languages) - The paper discusses work stealing, which is a programming technique used in multithreaded programming languages. 
5. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper analyzes the behavior of work stealing in multithreaded computations, which can be seen as a system, and provides upper bounds on the number of steals, which is related to control.
